# Generic UI (`components/ui`, **`components/shared`**)

Composable building blocks live under **`components/shared`** (composed controls, shells, selectors); **`components/ui`** holds primitives.
Components in **`ui`** + **`shared`** must stay **reusable**: names, file names, and public props describe **layout and behavior**, not one feature (no “recipe / ingredient / pantry” specificity in shared layers).

Put **section-specific** UI under **`components/<section>/`** (e.g. **`components/ingredients/ingredients-catalog.tsx`**, **`components/recipes/meal-ingredients-editor.tsx`**) and import from **`app/**/page.tsx`**. You may still use **`app/.../_name.tsx`** for thin route-only wrappers if needed. Never underscore **`page.tsx`** / **`layout.tsx`**.

**Avoid** domain-coupled names/props (**`RecipeCard`**, **`IngredientRow`**, **`props: Recipe`** from **`lib/data`** when you could express the same UI with generic props).

**Prefer** structural names (**`ImageSelector`**, **`EditableLineList`**) and map domain data at the call site (**`previewSrc`**, **`onSubmit`**, **`lines`**).

```tsx
export function RecipeMainImageFields({ recipe }: { recipe: Recipe }) {}

export function ImageSelector({ previewSrc, defaultImageUrl }: { previewSrc: string | null; defaultImageUrl: string }) {}
```

When **adding/editing** generic pieces ⇒ keep them in **`components/shared`** / **`components/ui`**; section/domain UI ⇒ **`components/<section>/`** (not **`components/ui`** or misleadingly specific **`shared`** names).

## Exception: **`features/`** (project root)

When domain UI is used from **both** a **route page** *and* the **assistant generated-UI shell**, place it under **`features/<name>/`** (client **`.tsx`** + optional **`*.actions.ts`**). See **components-features** for **`features/` vs `tools/`**.
